;Draft notes
*{{note label|Note1|a|a}}Edmonton's second-round pick will go to St. Louis, as the result of a trade on July 10, 2013 that sent [[David Perron]] to Edmonton, in exchange for [[Magnus Pääjärvi|Magnus Paajarvi]], and this pick.<ref>{{cite web|title=Blues Acquire Paajarvi from Oilers|url=http://blues.nhl.com/club/news.htm?id=677550|publisher=[[National Hockey League]]|date=July 10, 2013|accessdate=May 19, 2014}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note1|b|b}} The [[Calgary Flames]]' fourth-round pick went to the [[St. Louis Blues]] as the result of a trade on June 28, 2014 that sent [[Roman Polák|Roman Polak]] to Toronto in exchange for [[Carl Gunnarsson]] and this pick.<ref>{{cite web|title=Maple Leafs trade for Polak to change defense|url=http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=724354|publisher=National Hockey League|date=June 28, 2014|accessdate=June 28, 2014}}</ref><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Toronto previously acquired this pick as the result of a trade on September 29, 2013 that sent [[Joe Colborne]] to Calgary in exchange for this pick (being conditional at the time of the trade).<ref>{{cite web|title=Maple Leafs trade Colborne to Flames|url=http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=684670|date=September 29, 2013|accessdate=September 29, 2013}}</ref> The condition – If Calgary fails to qualify for the [[2014 Stanley Cup playoffs]] then this pick will remain a fourth-round pick in 2014 – was converted on March 30, 2014.
*{{note label|Note1|c|c}}Tampa Bay's fourth-round pick will go to St. Louis, as the result of a trade on July 10, 2012 that sent [[B. J. Crombeen]] and a fifth-round pick in [[2014 NHL Entry Draft|2014]] to Tampa Bay, in exchange for a fourth-round pick in [[2013 NHL Entry Draft|2013]], and this pick.<ref name="bjcrombeentrade">{{cite web|title=Blues Acquire Picks from TB for Crombeen|url=http://blues.nhl.com/club/news.htm?id=637599|publisher=St. Louis Blues|date=July 10, 2012}}</ref>
*St. Louis's fourth-round pick will go to the Nashville Predators, as the result of a trade on June 30, 2013 that sent a fourth-round pick in [[2013 NHL Entry Draft|2013]] to St. Louis, in exchange for a seventh-round pick in 2013, and this pick.<ref name=2013picktrades>{{cite web|title=Canucks-Devils trade highlights day of deals at draft|url=http://www.nhl.com/ice/news.htm?id=675991|publisher=[[National Hockey League]]|accessdate=May 19, 2014|date=June 30, 2013}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note1|d|d}}Calgary's fifth-round pick will go to St. Louis, as the result of a trade on July 5, 2013 that sent [[Kris Russell]] to Calgary, in exchange for this pick.<ref>{{cite web|title=Flames acquire Kris Russell from St. Louis|url=http://flames.nhl.com/club/news.htm?id=676671|publisher=[[Calgary Flames]]|date=July 5, 2013|accessdate=May 19, 2014}}</ref>
*St. Louis's fifth-round pick will go to the Tampa Bay Lightning, as the result of a trade on July 10, 2012 that sent fourth-round picks in [[2013 NHL Entry Draft|2013]] and [[2014 NHL Entry Draft|2014]] to St. Louis, in exchange for [[B. J. Crombeen]] and this pick.<ref name="bjcrombeentrade" />
*{{note label|Note1|e|e}}Boston's sixth-round pick will go to St. Louis, as the result of a trade on April 3, 2013 that sent [[Wade Redden]] to Boston, in exchange for this pick (being conditional at the time of the trade).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blues.nhl.com/club/news.htm?id=663827 |title=Blues Acquire Conditional Pick for Redden: The Blues get a conditional seventh round pick in 2014 for Wade Redden |publisher=[[National Hockey League]]|date=April 3, 2013}}</ref> The condition – St. Louis will receive a sixth-round pick in [[2014 NHL Entry Draft|2014]] if Redden appears in one playoff game in the [[2013 Stanley Cup playoffs|2013]] for the Bruins – was converted on May 1, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nhl.com/ice/recap.htm?id=2012030141|title=Bruins dominate Maple Leafs to win Game 1|publisher=[[National Hockey League]]|date=May 1, 2013}}</ref>

